The paper deals with the identification of linear time-varying systems, which is a topic in control theory and system identification. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses compressive sensing techniques to solve the identification problem, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the effect of measurement noise, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses numerical methods to analyze the method's sensitivity to noise, which falls under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper deals with the identification of complex dynamical systems, which is a topic in cs.DS (Dynamical Systems).
